{"type":"message","id":"ff703914","parentId":"64bfa608","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:56:02.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to check if this is valid. Looking at the earlier code, the embedding config requires \"apiKey\" and uses \"openai\" as the provider by default, not Ollama. Let me check if LanceDB supports other providers.\n\nActually, wait - looking at the code again:\n```javascript\nembedding: {\n  provider: \"openai\",\n  model,\n  apiKey: resolveEnvVars(embedding.apiKey),\n  baseUrl: typeof embedding.baseUrl === \"string\" ? resolveEnvVars(embedding.baseUrl) : void 0,\n  dimensions: typeof embedding.dimensions === \"number\" ? embedding.dimensions : void 0\n}\n```\n\nIt always sets provider to \"openai\" and calls resolveEnvVars on the apiKey. If I just set something like \"not-needed\", it might fail somewhere. \n\nLet me test if it will work after restarting the gateway, or revert to a simpler solution - just keep memory-core for now since it works fine.\n\nActually, thinking about it more - LanceDB isn't strictly necessary. The current memory system with SQLite backend (memory-core) is already working well. The vector search is a nice-to-have, but not required for a functional memory system.\n\nLet me explain the situation to the user and give them the choice.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d56d90ae89ef50b3ffaee4eec8cc6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw plugins doctor 2>&1 | tail -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":4323,"output":310,"cacheRead":47616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52249,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775278542110,"responseId":"019d56d8c6112ac440e5863b338cb39c"}}
