{"type":"message","id":"794faf39","parentId":"33dca902","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:56:22.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, looking at the code more carefully, LanceDB always uses the \"openai\" embedding provider regardless of what I configure - it just changes the model and baseUrl. So it's probably designed for OpenAI-compatible APIs.\n\nThe embedding API needs to be OpenAI-compatible. Ollama's embeddings API is actually OpenAI-compatible at `/api/embeddings`, so maybe it will work. Let me try restarting the gateway to see if it loads.\n\nActually, let's just try running the plugin doctor again to see if the slot config is valid.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe915473bfbb4c148c7d9f60","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw plugins doctor 2>&1 | grep -A5 \"memory\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":53168,"output":161,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53329,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775278579467,"responseId":"chatcmpl-056b2e17-2036-4a75-a426-3901dd1580a7"}}
