{"type":"message","id":"35475f2a","parentId":"a88746a6","timestamp":"2026-04-04T05:02:57.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if we can implement:\n1. Auto-correction writing (when user corrects me, automatically write to corrections.md)\n2. Framework-level hooks (like Claude Code's Auto Memory)\n\nLet me think about what's possible:\n\n1. **Auto-correction writing on user correction** - This could be done by:\n   - Detecting correction patterns in user messages (like \"不对\", \"实际上\", \"No, that's wrong\", \"应该\")\n   - But this requires analyzing every message, which is expensive\n   - Or we could train myself to recognize corrections and write them\n\n2. **Framework-level hooks** - This would require:\n   - Modifying OpenClaw core code\n   - Or creating a plugin that hooks into message processing\n   - This is more complex but could be done\n\nLet me check if there are any existing hooks in OpenClaw that we could leverage.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_72776259e8fb4f2a8f954ea1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"hook\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/*.js 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"self\\|improve\\|correction\\|memory\" | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":57071,"output":255,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57326,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775278972731,"responseId":"chatcmpl-363be337-da4a-4bd9-afd6-9ad379e3bc7c"}}
